<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="13">
Cyprinid fishes of the genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DA00CE7E-1535-4C6D-A1DC-6851CBB94B9B" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Balantiocheilos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Balantiocheilos Bleeker 1860:430" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Balantiocheilos Bleeker, 1860</taxonomicName>
(type species 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:816CFACE-25E1-49A9-A3A9-79EE794B0925" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Barbus melanopterus Bleeker 1851:11" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopterus">Barbus melanopterus Bleeker, 1851</taxonomicName>
) are easily distinguished from other members of the family by the presence of thick and fleshy lips, the lower lip bearing a large lobe that is deeply incised medially along its posterior edge and black along the distal margins of the dorsal, caudal, anal and pelvic fins. The posterior margin of the lower lip has often been described as forming a posteriorly opening pouch or pocket between the lip and the skin of the throat (e.g., Bleeker, 1863-64: 27, 80; Weber &amp; de Beaufort, 1916: 205; Smith, 1945: 206; Kottelat et al., 1993: 29, 110). To date, the genus has been considered monotypic and found only in river drainages of Sundaic and mainland Southeast Asia (Indochina). 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Balantiocheilos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hekouensis">Balantiocheilos hekouensis Wu, in Wu et al., 1977</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Paraspinibarbus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macracanthus">Paraspinibarbus macracanthus (Pellegrin &amp; Chevey, 1936)</taxonomicName>
(Chu &amp; Kottelat, 1989).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="13">
A comparison between Indochinese and Sundaic specimens previously thought to be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Balantiocheilos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="melanopterus">B. melanopterus</taxonomicName>
shows that two distinct species can be recognized, with the Indochinese specimens representing a new species described herein as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Balantiocheilos" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ambusticauda">Balantiocheilos ambusticauda</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
